        <methods>
            <methodStep>
                <description>
                    <section>
                        <title>Initial reclassification of MAG landuse dataset</title>
                        <para>The original MAG land use map contains 46 land use categories. They
                            were reclassified according to the following scheme. LUcodes 730
                            ("Passive open space") and 900 ("Vacant") were classified as "desert";
                            LUcode 750 ("Agriculture") classified as "agriculture"; LUcode 710
                            ("Active open space") classified as "Recreation"; all other land uses
                            are classified as "Urban", and "water" (LUcode 740) is left
                            unspecified.</para>
                    </section>
                    <section>
                        <title>Additional vacant land reclassification rules</title>
                        <para>1) If it was urban in 1995, it is urban. 2) If it is surrounded on all
                            sides by urban land, it is urban. 3) If it is next to desert or water or
                            agriculture and not next to urban land, it is desert. 4) If it is
                            surrounded on 3 sides by urban land and one side by water or
                            agriculture, it is urban. 5) If it is surrounded by agricultural and
                            urban with no other desert land near, it is urban. 6) If slivers were
                            not visible to the naked eye, it was urban. 7) If it is within a new
                            development area, it is urban.</para>
                    </section>
                    <section>
                        <title>Additional Active Open Space reclassification rules</title>
                        <para>1) If it was recreation in 1995 &#226;&#8364;&#8220; it is recreation. 2) If it is
                            shaped like a golf course and near another golf course &#226;&#8364;&#8220; it is
                            recreation. 3) If it was urban in 1995 &#226;&#8364;&#8220; it is urban. 4) If it is
                            surrounded by urban lands &#226;&#8364;&#8220; and was not recreation in 1995, it is
                            urban. 5) If it is within a new development area, it is urban.</para>
                    </section>
                    <section>
                        <title>Additional Passive Open space reclassification rules</title>
                        <para>1) If it was desert in 1995, it is desert. 2) If it was recreation in
                            1995, it is recreation 3) If it is within a new development area, it is
                            urban. 4) If it was urban in 1995, it is urban.</para>
                    </section>
                    <section>
                        <title>Additional Water reclassification rules</title>
                        <para>1) If it is a riverbed, it is desert. 2) If it is an urban lake or
                            canal, it is urban.</para>
                    </section>
                </description>
            </methodStep>
        </methods>
